        "<p>eliminated a superfluous Gipsy who makes her appearance towards the</p>\n<p>end of the tale _Ã  propos des boltes_, but otherwise have left the tale</p>\n<p>unaltered as one of the few English folk-tales that have been taken down</p>\n<p>from the mouths of the peasantry: this applies also to i., ii., xi.</p>\n<p>_Parallels_.-There is a magic snuff-box with a friendly power in it in</p>\n<p>Kennedy's _Fictions of the Irish Celts_, p.</p>\n<p>49.</p>\n",
